x4freetext: 1244Sn(n,g) result
This target was irradiated by the 22 MeV
polarized deuteron beam with a vector polarization
Metallic 124Sn (143 ug/cm2 thick) evaporated on a
carbon foil backing (about 4 ug/cm2 thick).
All spectra were normalized with respect to the beam
current accumulated by a Faraday cup.
Q3D magnetic spectrograph with the 90 cm long
focal plane detector with cathode-strip readout.
Statistical error
Systematic uncertainty mainly due to target
thickness uncertainty (15%)
Tables from Dr. Ivo Tomandl
